snippet.textDisplay:
When the world ends and the silver trumpets sound....ozzy will be there in the sky drawn from the clouds singing us to the ever after what ever it may be.

We don't have long left with him relative to how long we've had him. I am blessed as are we all, for being able to have lived with these amazing artists who orchestrated our thoughts, imaginations and our lives. I as a fan want to say thank you, most importantly, i want to say it while ozzy can read it with mortal eyes.

You'll always be there for me when I need words of wisdom, when I need to know someone understands, and when your long past the gates of the afterlife. Thank you, we all love you ozzy.

snippet.textDisplay: I love this song and what a great duo.  I feel this song can be applied to so many musicians past and present, those we have lost like Freddy Mercury and those who are still with us.  None of those musicians were or are ordinary men and women, they brought us joy and sadness both in the songs they sang and in their passing.  Ozzy "The Prince of Darkness" Osbourne and Sir Elton John will never be forgotten, and they are far from being ordinary men.
